annotation.TEXT: Yep, judging by how that coin bounced, that was definitely a custom block designed to be solid for enemies (and other non-player sprites) only.
Alright, I'm now back to feeling the power of toasty in a good way this time!
Good thing I decided to instinctively duck in this little ditch here!
Alright, so we are headed to Electricave!
"Mooving Ruins"? Shouldn't that be "Moving Ruins", with only one "o" in "Moving"? Or is this gonna be cow-themed? (Please be the latter!)
Oh, maybe I can get a 1-up stomping combo here?
BGM: Donkey Kong Country 3 - Hot Pursuit
Okay, now I doubt I'd ever play Irisu Syndrome, I have no idea how to go about having Mario reenact that Home Alone scene, I don't know what "What does the Fox say?" pertains to...

Argh, missed grabbing a "vine" again! I'm not a big fan of how picky SMW's fences can be when it comes to you grabbing them. SMW's actual vines are more player-friendly, but would the actual vines work well with the Hoopsters (fence koopas)?
Whoa, what the heck?! What's up with this weird saw and its abnormal homing capabilities?!
Yes, electricity usually does indeed hurt, so I'll try not to touch them!
2-life combo!
"Boiling Blue Bully Belt... Bloiling Bue Blully... Bleggh!" ...Yeah, screw that. (I could probably do it right with enough practice.)
Well, that star didn't last very long. I understand it was to ensure my safety as I was bouncing out of there, but you still could've let me enjoy it for a little longer...
D'oh! Jumped too high there.
Ow! The extreme corner of my shoe just felt the power of toasty! (Aww... I should've put in the "Toasty!" sound effect there.)
I don't know what disco beep blocks are, "Coin Jammer Lammy" is really funny, and...

What the heck? Why didn't I regrab the vine there? ...Oh, you know what? These vines are actually fences, which have an odd property where if you climb to the extreme left or right edge of one, then jump straight up, the game won't let you regrab the fence you just jumped from again unless you move sideways towards it.
Well, at least, thanks to midpoint, that previous hit I took doesn't matter.
Yeah, I took a hit there. Also, that 1-up is totally not worth it!
Now these Ninjis are feeling the power of toasty!
Awesome!
Alright, let's just backtrack a bit to see what that bonus area skipped...
Ahh! It's those electric jellyfish things from A Link to the Past! (Actually, it's a Boo ceiling, but that can still be troublesome.)
DOUBLE KILL!
Also, I doubt I could've gotten a 1-up stomping combo back there, so going for that flower right away didn't hurt me at all.
WAHHH!!! Oh, my god! Pokey, what have they done to you?!
Okay, it looks like I didn't miss anything else besides those three coins up there.
I'm not doing a very good job on these multi-coin blocks.

Oh, man! I just found a shiny Hoopster! Aw, but I made it faint with my spin jump... Nuts. (Actually, in my Pokémon X game, I did find a shiny Zangoose in a horde battle a couple weeks ago. And I think that's the first shiny I've found in the wild in an official Pokémon game since Gen. 3!)
Nope, I just stomp them. Oh, well. That's fine.
Huh? Nothing up here? Actually, it looks like I'm supposed to go down where the coins are here.
It's you!! How are you Hammer Brother!! You have no chance to survive make your time.
However, it appears that "Mooving Ruins" is indeed a typo, as I didn't see any cows there. So, either change "Mooving" to "Moving", or add a secret cow level or something like that there!
Is that it? Just a 1-up? Nuts.
Whoops. Ehh, I'll let that one Ninji live.
Whoops! There was that glitch where you can sometimes shoot fireballs through solid layer 2 objects for some reason.
I had unlocked Climbing Paradise to the northwest of Apple Jungle, and then I walked back around to Electricave, and then moved back to the level-less point, where I intended to end the episode.
Okay, that Hoopster up there has totally gotta be guarding something!
Oh, man. Those jellyfish aren't the only electric things around!

Whoa! And those are baseballs! (Maybe they're of the cowhide variety? ...Ehh, that would be a bit of a stretch, though. But, I bet the King of All Cosmos would definitely count those baseballs as cows!)
...28? I should've been able to get at least 40 with that saw's help. That's kind of lame.
...And, I just noticed a grammatical error right there in the "toasty" line. It should say "1 vote TO feel the power of toasty", not "1 vote FOR feel the power of toasty". Oops. Oh, well.
Ooh, coins!
Yep, this is totally a vertical level!
Alright, so we've got Hoopsters on vines. Are they rideable, like in SMB2?
Unless this is intentional, add an "s" to change "hurt" into "hurts".
Okay, please let this be a power up... Thank you!
Yes, I saw that vine up there!

If I was still super, I probably could've still gotten 30 or maybe 40 from the ground (or if I was ultra lucky, 50), but a small plumber has a significant disadvantage with this, and probably couldn't even reach 30...
And wow, this game really wanted to make sure I was fully powered up here, which makes me think this could get nasty!
BGM: CUSTOM - Athletic by MuimiMoji
So, where should I go after I find both exits here? Place your votes now as to whether I take the normal path or the secret path afterwards! To be continued...
Huh. Is that it? No moving platform, and no row of three coins just over the exit pit? Oh, well.
I wonder if I'll be able to perform a 1-up stomping combo with the Hoopsters somewhere in this level...
Whoa there, saw!
And, just as I expected, clearing Electricave just leads straight to Climbing Paradise, so I guess I'm going to do some climbing next!

Ah, so the next level is a red level called Kabu Katakomb. I'm going to assume that the use of "k"s instead of "c"s in "Katakomb" is intentional, and that the level will be themed around a particular Kirby enemy.
Alright! Party... time?
Oh, come on! I didn't actually visibly touch that Hoopster above me! But, since they're actually fence koopas, their hitbox is larger than they look...
At least you guys were still able to vote! So, let's see what the voting results were...
Ack! Why did I fail to grab the vine at first there?
At least the moles aren't made of electricity.
Nuts. Wasn't close enough to the Hammer Brother to continue the combo, but even if I was, I still would've been one stomp short of getting any 1-ups.
So what kinds of electric creatures are we talking about here?
And yeah, I'm typing out that entire Unhinged MTG card's name here.
Zwee! Halfway done, and still no cows (unless you count the baseballs).
Veni Vidi Vici!
Alright, I'm flowered up again.
I hope I didn't just break a potential 1-up combo by going for this flower.

That probably explains why I had trouble grabbing the short vine above a Lava Lotus earlier. And I bet these Hoopsters are actually fence koopas, with a custom block at the top of each "vine" made just to keep them from climbing onto the back side.
Whoa. Thought I mistimed that for a split-second.
BGM: Kirby's Epic Yarn - Outer Rings
Oh, man. Screen warp. Let me guess... I'm in a vertical level now, right?
Ah, it's that "Decisive Here We Go!" music again.
Goal tape average so far: 140 / 4 = 35 stars each.
Now, those two levels didn't take terribly long, so I've got time for one more...
Hello, and welcome back to Something else! Alright, now the first 20 seconds here is the footage that I accidentally left out of the end of the previous episode.
Goal tape average so far: 193 / 6 = 32.167 stars each.
Aww... It looks like it is just "Moving Ruins"... And, those are Ninjis, not cows!
Meh. Also, unfortunately, due to what the star counter is used for during the bonus game, I'll have to start over from 0 stars after each bonus game, regardless of how much I surpass the 100 mark by.
That sound effect was from Banjo-Kazooie, when the player collects a Mumbo token.
Monster combo! (10 hits)
Ooh, 1-up! Good thing I was holding right! Unfortunately, it looks like I'm gonna have to settle for a sub-par number of bonus stars here...
Goal tape average so far: 165 / 5 = 33 stars each.
Ah, more moving layer 2, but this time, it's a bit more malicious. Better stay alert.
